com.epoch.session

Class RegradeSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.session.RegradeSession
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EvalResultConstants

    public class RegradeSession
extends Object
implements EvalResultConstants
    Used to perform the forced regrade on a single question of an assignment when the question is changed after students have already begun to work it and the grades of some responses may change.

      • RegradeSession

        public RegradeSession(int hwId,
                      int hwNum,
                      int qId,
                      String instrId,
                      String studId,
                      GradeSet gset)
        Establishes a session for regrading a question in an assignment after it has been edited.
        Parameters:
        hwId - ID number of the assignment
        hwNum - 1-based serial number of the assignment
        qId - the unique ID number of the question to regrade, or 0 if all in the assignment are to be regraded
        instrId - login ID of the instructor
        studId - login ID of the one student whose grades are being recalculated, or null if all students' grades are being recalculated
        gset - used to recalculate modified grades

                   throws DBException,
                          NonExistentException,
                          ParameterException
        Reevaluates all responses to one or all questions in an assignment and rewrites the changed EvalResults.
        Returns:
        userIds of those students whose grades were changed.
        Throws:
        NonExistentException - if the question does not exist
        ParameterException - if the question has not been answered previously
        DBException - if the database can't be read or written to

      • doRegrade

        public String[] doRegrade(int qId)
                   throws DBException,
                          NonExistentException,
                          ParameterException
        Reevaluates all responses to one question in an assignment and rewrites the changed EvalResults in the gradebook.
        Parameters:
        qId - unique question ID of the Q currently being regraded
        Returns:
        userIds of those students whose grades of their most recent responses were changed
        Throws:
        NonExistentException - if the question does not exist
        ParameterException - if the question has not been answered previously
        DBException - if the database can't be read or written to
